00:34.960 --> 00:36.200
(ALL GROANING)

00:37.800 --> 00:38.801
(ALL GASPING)

00:40.640 --> 00:42.085
(ALL GROANING)

00:42.280 --> 00:45.045
WOMAN;
<i>Welcome to</i> Diversity Tales.

00:45.200 --> 00:46.486
(ALL GROANING)

00:46.720 --> 00:49.121
Enjoy your
multicultural hooey!

00:49.280 --> 00:50.406
(LAUGHS)

00:51.560 --> 00:53.562
WOMAN: <i>It was the
Feast of the Sea Lion</i>

00:53.640 --> 00:54.880
<i>Who Would Not Share.</i>

00:54.960 --> 00:58.169
<i>Come, Brother Titi. Let us
collect cha-cha sticks.</i>

00:58.240 --> 01:00.083
<i>I will make a headdress
for the wedding</i>

01:00.200 --> 01:02.043
<i>of Earth Turtle
and Moon Mongoose.</i>

01:02.120 --> 01:03.884
<i>You don't need
a headdress.</i>

01:04.000 --> 01:07.322
<i>Your most beautiful costume
is your self-esteem.</i>

01:07.680 --> 01:11.082
(WOMAN READING)

01:11.160 --> 01:12.571
What is this crap?

01:12.640 --> 01:14.927
This is worse than
<i>Wheelchair-Nocchio.</i>

01:15.000 --> 01:16.604
Yeah? Well, if you
don't like the movie,

01:16.720 --> 01:18.484
feel free to stare out the window.
(LAUGHS)

01:19.440 --> 01:20.441
(CAR POPS)

01:21.320 --> 01:24.767
Hey, crypt keeper, I like
your Dodge Scare-a-van!

01:24.880 --> 01:26.086
(ALL LAUGH)

01:26.240 --> 01:28.686
How dare you mock
my mobile-a-mobile?

01:28.840 --> 01:31.241
It was the first
car to outrun a man.

01:31.360 --> 01:32.805
A caveman!

01:32.920 --> 01:34.365
(ALL LAUGHING)

01:34.640 --> 01:37.644
I thought of that because I
slept in a cave last night.

01:37.720 --> 01:38.960
(HUFFS) Of all the...

01:39.040 --> 01:43.443
I will not be lampooned by school children!
Kill them, Smithers!

01:43.520 --> 01:45.807
Uh, you could just
buy a new car, sir.

01:45.880 --> 01:47.291
Well, whatever's easier.

01:47.360 --> 01:51.046
A new car? May I
suggest an Oldsmobile?

01:53.240 --> 01:54.924
Mr. Bums sucks!

01:55.120 --> 01:56.281
(LAUGHING)

01:57.160 --> 02:00.642
I won't forget who mocked me!
I'm taking your picture!

02:00.720 --> 02:04.281
Now hold perfectly
still for 78 minutes.

02:06.000 --> 02:07.365
(SNORING)

02:10.039 --> 02:11.769
(HOMER HUMMING)

02:16.040 --> 02:17.565
Doo-doo-doo-doo-doo-doo!

02:17.760 --> 02:18.966
Simpson!
Charge!

02:19.040 --> 02:20.041
I mean, yes, sir?

02:20.160 --> 02:21.491
I just bought a new car.

02:21.560 --> 02:22.800
A nice foreign number.

02:22.880 --> 02:25.850
The Lamborgotti Fasterossa.

02:25.920 --> 02:28.161
A Lamborgotti Fasterossa?

02:28.240 --> 02:31.244
That's the car I think about
when I make love to my wife.

02:31.320 --> 02:34.324
Yes. I need you to pick up my
car at the factory in Italy

02:34.400 --> 02:36.084
and ship it
directly back to me.

02:36.200 --> 02:37.964
I'll save thousands
in taxes.

02:38.040 --> 02:39.007
You're sending me to Italy?

02:39.080 --> 02:40.127
Yes.

02:40.200 --> 02:42.009
Can I take my family?
Sure.

02:42.080 --> 02:43.206
Do I have to
hang outwith them?

02:43.280 --> 02:44.566
It would be nice.

02:44.920 --> 02:46.729
(GROANS)

02:47.840 --> 02:48.921
Oh.

02:50.800 --> 02:52.006
Mmm? (STRUGGLES)

02:53.960 --> 02:57.851
Hey, that guy in first class is
taking a TV out of his armrest.

02:57.920 --> 02:59.126
What's in you?

02:59.240 --> 03:00.401
(GRUNTS AND GROANS)

03:00.480 --> 03:02.209
A bunch of stupid cables.

03:02.360 --> 03:03.361
(GRUNTS)

03:08.560 --> 03:12.610
Hey, Brandine! The kids
just got a new playhouse!

03:12.680 --> 03:17.971
Cletus, you are the most wonderful
husband and son I ever had.

03:22.680 --> 03:23.681
(BRAKES SCREECHING)

03:25.640 --> 03:28.166
What's with the Canadian
flag on your backpack?

03:28.280 --> 03:31.602
Well, some people in Europe
have the impression

03:31.680 --> 03:36.208
that America has made some stupid
choices in the past, oh, five years.

03:36.320 --> 03:38.527
So for the next week,
I'm from Canada.

03:38.600 --> 03:40.364
Uh, I think Dad may
blow your cover.

03:40.440 --> 03:43.046
That flag is mine!
Don't mess with Texas!

03:43.200 --> 03:45.601
Shock and awe, losers!
Shock and awe!

03:47.760 --> 03:51.048
Your car, she's coming
off the assembly line.

03:54.800 --> 03:56.404
(MACHINE WHIRRING)

03:56.920 --> 04:01.244
This car is the ultimate marriage
of design and technology.

04:01.480 --> 04:03.482
Ooh, marriage!

04:03.560 --> 04:05.688
Now we have to drive
it straight to Rome

04:05.760 --> 04:07.842
where it will be shipped to Mr.
Burns in Springfield.

04:07.920 --> 04:10.810
Gee, I wish we could explore
a little more of Italy.

04:10.880 --> 04:14.441
Marge, are you encouraging
me to be irresponsible?

04:14.520 --> 04:17.966
Why don't you encourage him to
get us some health insurance?

04:18.040 --> 04:19.451
Why you little... (GRUNTS)
(CHOKES)

04:21.959 --> 04:22.961
(BOTH CHOKING)

04:25.000 --> 04:26.206
Ow! D'oh!

04:26.320 --> 04:27.481
(GRUNTING)

04:29.760 --> 04:30.761
(BOTH GROANING)

04:32.120 --> 04:34.282
So, first time in Italy?

04:37.080 --> 04:39.128
HOMER: Wow.
I've seen photos of this.

04:39.200 --> 04:42.602
But you can't really experience
it until you're here!

04:42.680 --> 04:45.729
A McDonald's where
you can get booze!

04:46.040 --> 04:47.041
(GULPING)

04:47.720 --> 04:50.326
Dad, don't you want to turn
around and see the tower?

04:50.600 --> 04:52.807
Eh, there's a picture
of it on my cup.

04:55.200 --> 04:56.690
When Mount Vesuvius
erupted,

04:56.760 --> 04:59.889
people were overcome
by volcanic ash so fast

04:59.960 --> 05:02.122
that they were frozen in
whatever position they were in

05:02.200 --> 05:03.565
at the moment
of their death.

05:04.920 --> 05:06.001
Savages.

05:06.840 --> 05:09.605
We've passed the Ponte
Vecchio Bridge three times.

05:09.680 --> 05:10.761
I think we're lost.

05:10.840 --> 05:12.922
Let me check the navigation system.
(CLICKS)

05:13.040 --> 05:14.485
Says here we should turn left

05:14.560 --> 05:17.325
at a fat chick in a tutu
being fed by a midget.

05:17.400 --> 05:19.880
That's a DVD of
a Fellini movie.

05:19.960 --> 05:21.325
(CARNIVAL MUSIC PLAYING)

05:22.360 --> 05:25.364
I get it. The midget
represents dwarves.

05:25.440 --> 05:26.441
Dad, cheese truck!

05:27.480 --> 05:28.527
(ALL SCREAMING)

05:28.880 --> 05:31.724
(GASPS) Mozzarella!
Parmigiano! Provolone!

05:31.800 --> 05:34.406
Pecorino! Gorgonzola!
Fontina!

05:34.520 --> 05:36.522
Taleggio! Bocconcini!

05:37.360 --> 05:38.407
(CLATTERS)

05:39.600 --> 05:41.568
(ALL SCREAM)
LISA: Mortadella!

05:42.200 --> 05:43.201
(CRASHES)

05:44.520 --> 05:46.522
Don't worry. We got
the cheese insurance.

05:46.600 --> 05:48.204
It doesn't cover
mortadella.

05:48.280 --> 05:50.123
(GROANS) No!

05:51.440 --> 05:52.851
(ALL GRUNTING)

05:53.360 --> 05:56.091
Stupid Italy! I wish
you'd never been unified

05:56.160 --> 05:58.208
by Victor Emmanuel ll!

05:58.280 --> 06:01.762
If only you'd stayed a loose
confederation of city states

06:01.880 --> 06:04.451
trading with each other
and occasionally warring.

06:05.200 --> 06:07.646
Maybe there's a mechanic
in this Tuscan village.

06:07.800 --> 06:09.131
(LIQUID SPLASHING)

06:09.520 --> 06:12.842
Hey, do you know anything about
fixing sports cars? <i>Scusi?</i>

06:12.960 --> 06:16.646
It's a Lamborgotti
Fasterossa XT 550

06:16.720 --> 06:19.087
with ABS
Sport Tech Package!

06:19.360 --> 06:20.407
(SIGHS)

06:20.640 --> 06:21.687
<i>Americano?</i>

06:21.760 --> 06:24.525
Americana? What the hell
could that mean?

06:24.600 --> 06:27.251
Why can't you people learn
to speak my language?

06:27.320 --> 06:29.607
I learned to eat your food!

06:30.440 --> 06:32.886
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

06:33.080 --> 06:35.367
Hey, she says the mayor
speaks English.

06:35.440 --> 06:37.761
I honor you
and your country.

06:39.720 --> 06:40.767
(GASPS)

06:41.240 --> 06:43.163
"Kentucky"?
In Italian

06:43.240 --> 06:45.720
this means "whore!"
(GRUNTS)

06:47.640 --> 06:51.167
Excuse me, Mr. Mayor? They
say you speak English.

06:51.800 --> 06:53.165
Indeed I do.

06:54.040 --> 06:55.405
ALL: Sideshow Bob!

06:55.480 --> 06:56.720
(GASPS) The Simpsons!

06:56.840 --> 06:57.966
(ALL SCREAMING TOGETHER)

07:01.640 --> 07:02.766
BART: Sideshow Bob?

07:02.840 --> 07:07.209
Of all the <i>regioni</i> in all the
<i>villaggi</i> in all of <i>Italia,</i>

07:07.360 --> 07:10.250
you had to be
I! mayors of this one!

07:10.320 --> 07:12.891
I can assure you I'm as sorry to
see you as you are to see me.

07:12.960 --> 07:14.121
How did you wind up here?

07:14.200 --> 07:15.850
Yes. Tell us your story.

07:15.920 --> 07:17.888
But ii better have a beginning,
a middle, and an end.

07:17.960 --> 07:21.009
And you'd better make us
root for the protagonist!

07:21.480 --> 07:25.041
My tale begins after I had once
again attempted to murder Bart.

07:25.120 --> 07:27.009
Okay. So far
I'm rooting for you.

07:34.720 --> 07:36.768
<i>I needed a fresh start,
but where?</i>

07:41.160 --> 07:43.970
Not in this lifetime!

07:46.200 --> 07:47.201
Damn it!

07:48.360 --> 07:49.361
Never!

07:50.560 --> 07:52.130
Now cut that out!

07:55.600 --> 07:59.321
Ah, Tuscany. Fortune is
finally smiling upon me.

08:00.640 --> 08:02.563
(GRUMBLING)

08:07.720 --> 08:09.802
<i>I left my past
behind and moved</i>

08:09.920 --> 08:11.968
<i>to the small
village of Salsiccia.</i>

08:12.400 --> 08:14.448
<i>Acceptance came slowly.</i>

08:14.520 --> 08:17.683
It's pronounced <i>“buongiorno.“</i>

08:17.760 --> 08:19.489
Your mouth is getting lazy
on the second syllable.

08:19.600 --> 08:21.284
Here. Let me guide you.

08:23.440 --> 08:26.410
<i>But that all changed
when the grape harvest began.</i>

08:26.560 --> 08:27.686
(CROWD GRUNTING)

08:28.920 --> 08:31.048
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

08:38.280 --> 08:39.405
(ALL GASPING)

08:41.159 --> 08:43.527
(SINGING) <i>These feet are
made for stomping</i>

08:43.600 --> 08:45.602
<i>And that's just
what they'll do</i>

08:45.680 --> 08:50.561
<i>One of these days these feet
will make chianti out of you!</i>

08:50.960 --> 08:53.088
Ready, feet? Start stomping!

08:53.280 --> 08:55.282
(HUMMING)

08:56.440 --> 08:57.521
(CROWD CHEERING)

08:59.800 --> 09:01.723
<i>it was the biggest
harvest ever.</i>

09:01.840 --> 09:03.842
(CORK POPS) <i>Never had I
felt such acceptance.</i>

09:05.840 --> 09:08.889
<i>The next spring,</i> the contadini
<i>elected me their mayor.</i>

09:08.960 --> 09:12.089
<i>But! won more than
the love of a town.</i>

09:12.160 --> 09:14.367
Roberto, <i>amore!</i>

09:14.840 --> 09:18.731
This is my bride Francesca.
And my son, Gino.

09:18.800 --> 09:20.529
Holy moley!

09:20.600 --> 09:23.888
I always thought you were, you
know, out, loud, and proud!

09:24.000 --> 09:26.765
Well, I experimented
in college, as one does.

09:26.840 --> 09:28.649
Yeah. I never
went to college.

09:28.760 --> 09:29.966
Stop the presses.

09:30.040 --> 09:33.761
Hello. I'm Marge.
This is my husband Homer,

09:33.840 --> 09:36.127
my daughters
Lisa and Maggie,

09:36.200 --> 09:38.043
and my son
Bart Simpson.

09:38.120 --> 09:39.929
Bart Simpson?

09:40.000 --> 09:42.606
The name Roberto cries
when he has the bad dream.

09:42.680 --> 09:46.048
Bart Simpson! Bart Simpson!
Ban Simpson!

09:46.160 --> 09:49.687
I make like my daddy! I cut, cut...
(CHUCKLES)

09:49.880 --> 09:55.489
Yes. Ban and I used
to go fly-fishing together.

09:55.800 --> 09:58.610
Die, Bart! Die, Bart!

09:58.680 --> 09:59.727
(GRUMBLING)

10:02.520 --> 10:04.249
You shall all slay
for dinner

10:04.320 --> 10:07.688
and tell me more
about my wonderful Roberto.

10:08.080 --> 10:12.881
(SIGHS) He makes love like a
man who just got out of jail.

10:12.960 --> 10:13.961
Mmm. (KISSES)

10:14.040 --> 10:17.123
(CHUCKLES) Yes, yes,
you crave my skillful touch.

10:17.200 --> 10:21.125
Now go. Take the boy. And shut the door.
I'll rock your world anon.

10:21.200 --> 10:23.282
Simpsons, I beg of you,

10:23.360 --> 10:25.840
please don't destroy the new
life I've created here.

10:25.920 --> 10:29.970
Surely even the most heinous
criminal deserves a seventh chance!

10:30.040 --> 10:31.883
Bob, you haven't told
your wife

10:31.960 --> 10:33.849
about all the terrible
things you've done?

10:33.920 --> 10:35.649
Yeah. I tell Marge
everything.

10:35.720 --> 10:38.644
Not necessarily in words,
but in body language.

10:38.720 --> 10:40.484
You know, sneaking
around and such.

10:40.560 --> 10:42.801
Bob, your family
will find out the truth.

10:42.880 --> 10:45.167
Sooner or later,
you'll try lo kill me again.

10:45.240 --> 10:46.321
Watch. I'll prove it.

10:46.400 --> 10:49.404
Come on, Bob. Slice,
dice, and serve on rice.

10:49.480 --> 10:51.926
(CHUCKLES) You little scamp.

10:53.000 --> 10:56.083
You know, you'll make some
murderer very happy one day.

10:56.160 --> 10:58.049
But it shan't be me.

10:58.120 --> 11:01.010
Bart, Bob
is a family man now.

11:01.080 --> 11:04.243
You can't be a bad person
if you have a family.

11:04.320 --> 11:06.891
And literature is filled
with tales of redemption

11:06.960 --> 11:10.328
from Jean Valjean, to the voice
of Buzz Lightyear, Tim Allen.

11:10.440 --> 11:11.441
All right, Bob,

11:11.520 --> 11:13.090
we won't tell your
beautiful new family

11:13.160 --> 11:14.844
that you're a homicidal
psychopath

11:14.920 --> 11:16.763
if you fix up our car.

11:17.920 --> 11:19.524
Now, I can't undo
the past.

11:19.600 --> 11:21.489
But I can try to
make it up to you.

11:21.600 --> 11:24.683
My humble little
town is at your service.

11:26.280 --> 11:29.124
<i>Questi sono i miei amici,
 i</i> Simpsons!

11:29.240 --> 11:30.446
(CROWD CHEERING)

11:33.320 --> 11:36.449
(WHISPERS) Dad, don't
act like Mussolini.

11:36.520 --> 11:38.045
Ooh, I thought I was
doing Donald Trump.

11:38.240 --> 11:39.241
Hmph-hmph!

11:42.280 --> 11:43.770
Here's a cute fact.

11:43.840 --> 11:47.003
This sausage shop has been
grinding the same family of pigs

11:47.080 --> 11:48.923
for six hundred years.

11:49.000 --> 11:50.968
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

11:55.680 --> 11:56.727
<i>Prego.</i>

11:56.800 --> 11:57.881
<i>Si, si.</i>

11:58.800 --> 11:59.801
Ooh.

12:01.600 --> 12:02.761
(GOBBLING)

12:04.040 --> 12:06.407
And he kisses you
with that mouth?

12:06.480 --> 12:08.289
(MUFFLED)
I love you, Marge!

12:08.360 --> 12:09.771
(KISSING NOISES)

12:09.880 --> 12:10.881
(LAUGHING)

12:11.000 --> 12:12.126
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

12:12.320 --> 12:14.163
(CHILDREN GIGGLING)

12:18.840 --> 12:20.001
(LAUGHING)

12:20.480 --> 12:24.565
He's so wonderful. They
must miss him in America.

12:24.840 --> 12:26.490
Uh, well...

12:27.280 --> 12:29.248
(GUNS COCK)
Eat justice, Sideshow Bob!

12:35.400 --> 12:38.483
Chief, I tried to warn you. Sideshow
Bob hasn't lived here for months.

12:38.560 --> 12:40.847
Oh, God, am I sorry!
(CHUCKLES SHEEPISHLY)

12:41.160 --> 12:43.083
Oh, hey, is that
a Penn State banner?

12:43.160 --> 12:44.605
Because, um,
my cousin went there.

12:44.680 --> 12:47.160
Did you know him?
Mark Wiggum? Fat kid?

12:47.840 --> 12:49.126
Played a lot of <i>Tetris.</i>

12:50.120 --> 12:51.121
(GLASS CLINKS)

12:52.000 --> 12:53.001
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

12:53.080 --> 12:55.606
We are here to honor my old
friends, the Simpsons.

12:55.680 --> 12:59.446
Tomorrow they return to America,
taking with them my gratitude,

12:59.520 --> 13:04.367
my friendship, and my heartfelt
wish that they never return.

13:04.440 --> 13:06.329
And now, <i>mangiate!</i>

13:09.200 --> 13:11.806
No wine for her!
She's only eight!

13:11.880 --> 13:14.360
Marge, don't be
so Olive Garden.

13:14.480 --> 13:18.246
Yeah, this is Italy. Look, the
town drunk is two years old!

13:18.760 --> 13:21.843
(SINGING) <i>Hey, mambo
Mambo Italiano!</i>

13:21.920 --> 13:23.081
(BURPS)

13:23.440 --> 13:24.521
(GULPS)

13:35.240 --> 13:41.361
Bob, your generosity and <i>abbondanza
</i> have touched our hearts.

13:41.680 --> 13:43.250
(CHEERING)

13:44.080 --> 13:47.880
Bravo! Bravo! <i>Bravissimo!</i>

13:49.240 --> 13:50.241
Ooopsie.

13:50.360 --> 13:52.966
I'll just get it
outwith more wine.

13:53.040 --> 13:55.771
See? lt's fine.
Go on. Go on with the thing.

13:55.960 --> 13:56.961
Hmm.

13:57.200 --> 14:00.647
It's obvious why Bob is a vaunted
pillar of your community.

14:00.720 --> 14:04.361
Yeah. But he's a wanted
killer in our community!

14:04.480 --> 14:06.289
(LAUGHS)

14:09.080 --> 14:11.765
He deserves to be
hailed at this wingding.

14:11.840 --> 14:14.366
More like jailed
at Sing Sing!

14:14.440 --> 14:16.488
Time for bed now.
(CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)

14:16.960 --> 14:20.009
Drunken children
tell the ugliest lies.

14:20.200 --> 14:21.201
(CHUCKLES)

14:21.600 --> 14:23.648
Mmm. (GIGGLES)

14:27.200 --> 14:28.281
(SCREAMS)

14:28.720 --> 14:29.801
(CROWD GASPS)

14:29.920 --> 14:31.365
(SCREAMS) Sideshow Bob!

14:31.440 --> 14:33.044
Sideshow Bob?

14:33.120 --> 14:34.406
(SPEAKS ITALIAN)

14:34.720 --> 14:35.721
BOTH: Hmm?

14:50.720 --> 14:54.088
Roberto, is this true? You
tried to make the murder?

14:54.160 --> 14:56.606
But darling, the boy
drove me to murder

14:56.680 --> 14:58.330
by exonerating a harlequin

14:58.400 --> 15:01.165
who I framed for robbery
at the Kwik-E-Mart!

15:01.520 --> 15:04.410
Oh, it all sounds
so stupid.

15:04.480 --> 15:10.362
You have brought shame upon our
humble, Mafia-controlled village!

15:10.440 --> 15:13.250
You are welcome
in Salsiccia no more!

15:13.320 --> 15:14.321
(GRUNTS)

15:14.720 --> 15:15.721
(BLEATS)

15:15.880 --> 15:17.166
(SNARLS)

15:17.320 --> 15:18.367
Uh-oh.

15:18.440 --> 15:20.010
He's getting that
stabby look.

15:21.680 --> 15:23.045
Simpson family,

15:23.120 --> 15:29.480
I hereby swear a vendetta!

15:29.800 --> 15:33.521
"Vendetta" means "vendetta!"
(ALL SCREAMING)

15:36.520 --> 15:40.411
Boy, that Sideshow Bob goes from
zero to murder awfully fast.

15:40.480 --> 15:43.370
At least this time it was
Lisa who ruined Bob's life.

15:43.520 --> 15:45.443
(GROANS) I feel so sick.

15:45.520 --> 15:46.521
(CHUCKLES)

15:46.600 --> 15:48.648
It's called
a hangover, sweetie.

15:48.760 --> 15:50.842
And it's an unavoidable
part of life.

15:50.920 --> 15:52.251
MR. BURNS:
<i>Simpson! Simpson!</i>

15:52.320 --> 15:55.802
<i>Where is my roadster? You
were due back a month ago.</i>

15:55.880 --> 15:59.248
Mr. Burns, we may be experiencing
some technical difficulties.

16:00.720 --> 16:02.165
Ah...
(HUFFS)

16:04.560 --> 16:05.561
Sideshow Bob!

16:07.200 --> 16:08.201
(TIRES SCREECHING)

16:10.640 --> 16:13.928
(GASPS) Dad, you're driving
on an ancient Roman aqueduct!

16:14.000 --> 16:15.764
What am I supposed
to use it for?

16:15.840 --> 16:18.241
Transporting water
to distant urban centers?

16:25.640 --> 16:26.687
Uh-oh.

16:27.440 --> 16:28.805
Lazy Romans!

16:29.880 --> 16:31.291
(ALL SCREAMING)

16:31.360 --> 16:32.964
(BANG)
ALL: Huh?

16:34.440 --> 16:36.090
HOMER: Everyone remember
where we parked.

16:39.320 --> 16:40.446
(WHIMPERS)
(GRUNTS)

16:42.080 --> 16:43.127
Come on!

16:43.560 --> 16:44.846
(CRYING)

16:45.440 --> 16:49.411
Why do I keep
trying to kill them?

16:49.880 --> 16:50.927
Roberto!

16:51.000 --> 16:53.571
Francesca,
you've come to me!

16:53.640 --> 16:55.244
Well, you've caught me
at the right time

16:55.320 --> 16:59.166
because I swear never to raise
this hand in vengeance again.

16:59.240 --> 17:00.446
Hey, no, Roberto.

17:00.520 --> 17:02.409
If the Simpsons
have dishonored you,

17:02.480 --> 17:04.448
they have dishonored
our family.

17:04.520 --> 17:07.126
And we shall take
revenge as a family.

17:07.599 --> 17:10.922
Vendetta! Vendetta!
Vendetta for mi papa!

17:13.760 --> 17:17.320
Ah! Revenge is a dish
best served

17:17.400 --> 17:19.528
family-style.

17:20.119 --> 17:23.920
(EVIL LAUGH)

17:25.520 --> 17:26.567
(CRYING)

17:28.880 --> 17:29.961
(EVIL LAUGH)

17:31.480 --> 17:34.370
We're in a foreign city,
with no car,

17:34.440 --> 17:36.602
being stalked
by a killer.

17:36.680 --> 17:38.489
I feel like I'm in
<i>The Bourne Identity.</i>

17:38.960 --> 17:39.961
(BRAKES SCREECH)

17:41.120 --> 17:43.487
Hey, Krusty's in an opera
here in Rome.

17:43.640 --> 17:46.041
He can save our lives.
Come on, let's go!

17:46.240 --> 17:47.241
(GROANS) Oh!

17:47.400 --> 17:50.165
Opera? They have that
here, too?

17:50.400 --> 17:51.401
(GROANS)

17:52.000 --> 17:53.843
Let's see... Uh-huh.

17:54.040 --> 17:55.405
I ain't doing that.

17:55.480 --> 17:57.164
That's not funny.

17:57.240 --> 18:01.768
Here we'll change "wealthy merchant"
to "nudist with big rack."

18:01.840 --> 18:04.366
This needs punching up.
That's coming out.

18:04.440 --> 18:05.487
Two acts?

18:05.560 --> 18:06.766
Krusty, you gotta
help us!

18:06.840 --> 18:08.001
I don't do "gotta."

18:08.080 --> 18:10.890
Sideshow Bob has sworn
a vendetta against us!

18:10.960 --> 18:14.169
Vendetta? What's that?
An Italian vending machine?

18:17.200 --> 18:19.407
Ahhh! That's my opening joke,

18:19.480 --> 18:24.168
and my closer, and my saver,
and my topper! (SOBS)

18:24.360 --> 18:25.521
Please help us, Krusty.

18:25.600 --> 18:28.251
We don't want to be the first
Christians to die at the Coliseum.

18:28.320 --> 18:29.560
I'll tell you what.

18:29.640 --> 18:31.324
Put on these costumes.
Go on the stage

18:31.440 --> 18:33.090
and mix in with
the crowd scenes.

18:33.160 --> 18:35.128
He won't kill you in front
of all those witnesses.

18:35.200 --> 18:36.964
Can I be the
Phantom of the Opera?

18:37.040 --> 18:38.804
Dad, the Phantom
isn't in this.

18:38.880 --> 18:40.962
But I do a great
impression of him!

18:41.360 --> 18:42.441
(HUMS)

18:42.520 --> 18:44.602
l am the gayest
super villain ever!

18:44.680 --> 18:46.887
Beware my scented candles!

18:47.160 --> 18:48.889
Ooh. Scented!

18:49.160 --> 18:53.051
(SINGING)
<i>No more Rice Krispies</i>

18:53.120 --> 18:57.125
<i>We are out of Rice Krispies</i>

18:57.240 --> 18:58.446
(SOBS)

18:59.040 --> 19:00.201
(AUDIENCE GASPS)

19:01.040 --> 19:03.247
Hey, don't blame me.
I didn't write this crap.

19:03.320 --> 19:06.290
I can't believe what that clown
is doing to Leoncavallo!

19:06.360 --> 19:07.885
And they call me
a murderer!

19:13.760 --> 19:15.330
Vendetta! Vendetta!

19:15.400 --> 19:17.323
I don't wish to brag.
Vendetta! Vendetta!

19:17.400 --> 19:20.449
But he's evil at an
eighth grade level.

19:20.520 --> 19:22.682
Vendetta! Vendetta!

19:22.760 --> 19:24.808
Let's see.
What else we got here.

19:25.760 --> 19:28.331
So I had this
beautiful tour guide, right?

19:28.400 --> 19:30.767
And I tell her,
"I wanna see your Naples."

19:30.840 --> 19:32.126
She slapped me!

19:32.240 --> 19:33.241
(LAUGHS)

19:34.280 --> 19:35.691
We call it Napoli!

19:35.760 --> 19:38.525
Yeah? Well, it sounds like
you're all taking a Napoli!

19:38.600 --> 19:41.206
Know you're out there!
I can hear you being greasy!

19:41.280 --> 19:42.281
Ahhh!

19:42.640 --> 19:44.768
(SINGING OPERA)

19:51.160 --> 19:52.161
(APPLAUSE)

19:52.480 --> 19:54.244
That's so beautiful.

19:54.320 --> 19:56.049
That's Sideshow Bob!

19:56.120 --> 19:58.122
I know. And he's magic!

20:03.400 --> 20:07.007
This is no act! They're
actually trying to kill us!

20:07.080 --> 20:08.127
(AUDIENCE GASPS)

20:08.840 --> 20:11.161
(CONTINUES SINGING OPERA)

20:22.520 --> 20:23.601
(AUDIENCE SIGHS)

20:23.800 --> 20:25.404
(SPEAKING ITALIAN)

20:27.200 --> 20:28.486
(EVIL LAUGH)

20:34.760 --> 20:36.046
Quick! Get in!

20:38.600 --> 20:40.250
Krusty, you saved us!

20:40.320 --> 20:42.084
Well, I need someone
to help me

20:42.160 --> 20:44.083
smuggle antiquities
to America.

20:44.160 --> 20:47.084
Everyone break off a piece
and hide it on your person.

20:47.160 --> 20:48.366
Hide it well.

20:48.440 --> 20:51.250
Vendetta! Vendetta!
Vendetta!

20:52.840 --> 20:53.921
<i>Farfalla!</i>

20:54.000 --> 20:55.331
<i>Farfalla</i> vendetta!

20:57.200 --> 20:58.850
<i>Farfalla</i> vendetta!

21:00.480 --> 21:02.005
GINO: Farfalla <i>vendetta!</i>

21:07.480 --> 21:10.848
Oh, Homie,
isn't Venice romantic?

21:10.920 --> 21:13.844
This gondola ride
was a wonderful idea.

21:14.400 --> 21:17.131
(SINGING)
<i>When a wife looks like that</i>

21:17.200 --> 21:20.682
<i>And her husband's so fat,
that's immoral</i>

21:21.280 --> 21:23.123
<i>When she kisses that jerk</i>

21:23.200 --> 21:25.123
<i>While I do
all the work, that's...</i>

21:25.200 --> 21:26.361
Hey, knock it off!

21:26.520 --> 21:28.363
<i>Mi scusi.</i>
No speak English.

21:28.440 --> 21:33.204
(SINGING)
<i>When a big tub of lard...</i>
